{
  "stem": "2004.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Obviously, lumber yards usually are located near railroad stations.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And we saw the Jewish population being loaded up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Unfortunately, I never saw my parents because there were quite a number of them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I could never spot them at the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Maybe, perhaps when I got back-- when they took us back to work in that lumber yard, my parents might have been already loaded up into the closed sort of the cattle trains, cattle wagons.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we could never-- I could never see them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it's kind of difficult to sort of explain.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we had the feeling that we were never going to see our parents again.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was-- it's a little difficult to explain what it was like.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was a feeling that-- we were hoping that they were really going to-- the story was that they were going to be taken over to another camp and for work.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we had a feeling that this was not the case, even though we had no hard evidence at the time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the feeling was that these people were never going to survive the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were going to be taken over and done away with.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The way they were treated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The way we were treated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we knew that the basic feeling was-- the basic-- the final solution, we read about the final solution.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We knew what the final solution was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'd never read but people in our group did read And we were told in no uncertain terms that as soon as we are no longer needed, we will be destroyed.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Our only hope was that the war was going to end, and they never-- that it was going to end before they had a chance to destroy us all.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
